<note id="fs-id1165043262496" class="checkpoint">
<exercise id="fs-id1165043428512">
<problem id="fs-id1165043119394">
<para id="fs-id1165043119396">Use the first derivative test to find all local extrema for <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>f</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mroot><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mroot><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1165043305742">
<para id="fs-id1165042982077"><m:math><m:mi>f</m:mi></m:math> has no local extrema because <m:math><m:msup><m:mi>f</m:mi><m:mo>′</m:mo></m:msup></m:math> does not change sign at <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</solution>
<commentary id="fs-id1165042604838" type="hint">
<title>Hint</title>
<para id="fs-id1165042608705">The only critical point of <m:math><m:mi>f</m:mi></m:math> is <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</commentary>
</exercise>
</note>
